11:T482,<h1>eforge Configuration Reference</h1>
<p>eforge merges configuration from three tiers (highest precedence first):</p>
<ol>
<li><code>.eforge/config.yaml</code> — project-local, gitignored, developer-personal</li>
<li><code>eforge/config.yaml</code> — project-level, committed</li>
<li><code>~/.config/eforge/config.yaml</code> — user-global</li>
</ol>
<h2>Top-level fields</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Field</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>agents</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>build</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>daemon</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>hooks</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>langfuse</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>maxConcurrentBuilds</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>monitor</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>plan</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>plugins</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>prdQueue</code></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2>JSON Schema</h2>
<p>The complete machine-readable schema is at <a href="/schemas/config.schema.json"><code>/schemas/config.schema.json</code></a>.</p>
